snippet.title: Lost in Phoenix
snippet.description:
We drive by these people every day, we ignore them, shun them & refuse to understand their situation. They’re almost invisible to us because we can’t bother ourselves with asking how we can better understand & help these people in need. I’ll go out & capture their stories & help in whatever way I can. I invite you to like, subscribe & help by donating blankets, toiletries, food etc that I can hand out. Here is my cellphone in case you have a family member or friend you’d like for me to keep an eye out when I’m in the street talking to folks. 602-930-1289.  Follow me on Twitter @LostinPhx and on Snapchat Art2doe also an easy way to help this cause is by subscribing, sharing and hitting the notification bell. If you’d like to help beyond that, just text or call me and for those that want to donate here’s cashapp $LostInPhoenix 

https://linktr.ee/LostinPhoenix

Mail donations to:

Art Castro
2632 S. 83rd Ave 
Suite 100-240
Phoenix, AZ 85043
